    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-02-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-02-26T20:05:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Agricultural Business Security Tax Credit Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a retailer of agricultural products and chemicals or a manufacturer, formulator, or distributor of certain pesticides a business tax credit for 30 percent of costs for or related to the protection of such chemicals or pesticides, including employee security training and background checks, installation of security equipment, and computer network safeguards. Sets a $2 million annual limit on such credit and a per facility limitation of $100,000 (reduced by credits received for the five prior taxable years). Terminates such credit after 2012.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
